  <summary date="2021-06-25T11:45:41Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Shareholder Protection Act of 2021

This bill requires shareholder authorization of certain political expenditures by a publicly traded company. A violation of this requirement is considered&#160;a breach of fiduciary duty, and the officers and directors who authorized the expenditure are subject to joint and several liability. A publicly traded company must require a board vote with respect to political expenditures in excess of $50,000 and, within 48 hours, make publicly available the individual votes of each board member.</summary>
